HTTP Action

Call internal and external web services from OmniScript without coding or making Salesforce API calls using the HTTP Action.

Use the HTTP Action to:

Send GET, POST, PUT, or DELETE requests to standard REST Endpoints.
Call Apex REST.
Access Salesforce Named Credential (OAuth) identity services.

Settings:

HTTP Path: The request URL of the API.
HTTP Method: The method name.
Option Source: The type of HTTP Action.
Remote Timeout: The timeout for the request, in milliseconds.
Pre- and Post-Transform Data Mapper Interface: (Optional) Omnistudio Data Mapper Transform interface to run before or after the REST Action.

Prior to Summer '17, the HTTP Action was known as the REST Action.
